In Washburn County:  Robert John Kaiser appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Darryl L Christensen in court with attorney William Andrew Mayer.  Defendant Darryl L Christensen in custody.  AS - clerk.  9:10am. Court calls case and appearances.  Court speaks re: motion to vacate plea and briefs that were filed.  Atty Mayer speaks to the court. State speaks to the court re: witnesses and defendants motion.  Atty Mayer calls the defendant Darryl Christensen to the stand. Clerk swears in.  Atty Mayer begins questioning.  Atty Mayer offers exhibit 1-plea questionnaire and waiver of rights form. Exhibit 1-received.  Atty Mayer continues questioning. Nothing further.  Cross from the state.  State references transcript from sentencing. State continues questioning. Nothing further. Redirect from Atty Mayer. Nothing further. Witness is excused.  Recess at 9:43am.  Back on record at 9:57am.  No objections that Atty Aaron Nelson testify via telephone. State calls Atty Nelson. Court swears in. State begins questioning.  Court reviews defendants testimony with Atty Nelson.  Court finds that the defendant has waived his attorney-client privilege.  Court orders Atty Nelson to testify. State continues questioning.  Objection from Atty Mayer-overruled-State continues questioning.  Court speaks to Atty Nelson. Court questions Atty Nelson re: journal and note taking. Court makes record re: Atty Nelsons testimony. Atty Nelson speaks to the court.  State continues questioning.  Nothing further. Cross from Atty Mayer.  Nothing further. Redirect from the State.  Atty Nelson speaks to the parties. Court questions def. re: Attorney-client privilege.   Defendant requests to speak with Atty Mayer.  Recess at 10:43.  Back on record at 10:45am. Defendant waives privilege. Atty Nelson makes statement re: file being given to an Attorney in Milwaukee.  Nothing further.  Witness excused.  State rests.  Court speaks to Attorney Mayer re: time limits for a decision.  Def. to request an extension.  Oral ruling scheduled for June 19, 2019 at 01:00 pm.
